comment:
Amber Heard is a well documented, and self confessed liar.  She pled guilty to falsifying official documents in Australia, and Mr. Depp paid her fines and made a deal to appear in a public service video with her, although he had nothing to do with her smuggling her dogs into Australia, in order to gain her freedom.  Ms. Heard has *never* told the same story of abuse twice...which is a red flag to those of us who deal with narcissistic abuse.  She also has a history of domestic abuse.  In 2009, long before she met Mr. Depp, she was arrested for the domestic assault of her partner, Tasya van Ree.  The assault was witnessed by the arresting officers and an international airport full of people.  Although neither she, or Ms. van Ree (who confirmed to the officers that she wanted Ms. Heard arrested), contested the arrest...Ms. Heard would attempt to expunge the arrest from her record when she met Mr. Depp.  When the press uncovered the arrest, Ms. Heard suborned her *VICTIM* , Tasya van Ree, to write a statement to clear her name, but the arresting officer, Officer Beverly Leonard went public to expose Amber Heard's lies.

Amber Heard is a narcissistic abuser, and the *WORST* type of *FAKE* "feminist".  "Treat me just like a man, unless that means that you are going to hold me accountable for my crimes."  In my country, Judge Nicol would have lost his position for not recusing himself from the case due to his son's working relationship with Dan Wooton (much less he and his wife's connections to Ms. Heard's lawyers!)!  Rest assured Judge Nicol will be exposed when Amber Heard offends again.  Narcissistic abusers do not (can not) stop abusing.  They repeat their established patterns.  Eventually, someone will be hit by a thrown vodka bottle and be severely injured or killed...unless the Virginia Trial puts an end to Ms. Heard's crimes--which, by the evidence Mr. Depp's team has uncovered, seems highly likely.  If someone ends up hurt, Judge Nicol will only have his biased self to blame.
